Commentary: OUT! BOWLED'EM! Josh Tongue gets the big breakthrough for England right on the stroke of Lunch on Day 1. Tongue serves this one on a good length around off, bowling down the slope and this one just comes back in sharply with the angle. Usman Khawaja makes an assured leave but is completely bamboozled as the ball knocks over the top of off stump. Khawaja departs after a bit of a sluggish knock and Tongue's expensive start with the ball has proved to be fruitful in the end for England.

Commentary: OUT! STUMPED! Joe Root delivers big time for England! Gives the ball air and serves it outside off, Travis Head is tempted in the flight and looks to go down the ground. He shimmies down the track and goes through the shot. He is nowhere near the pitch of the ball. The ball spins away sharply and beats him on the outside edge. Jonny Bairstow collects it cleanly and removes the bails with his left glove. Travis Head is nowhere close to the crease and this is a much-needed breakthrough for England.

Commentary: OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Joe Root has two in the over and Australia have now lost half their side! Root comes from 'round the wicket and bowls it short, around off, Cameron Green goes back in the crease and tries to pull this one away. Gets into an awkward position and gets the ball from the splice of his bat. Skies it high in the air and only as far as mid on. James Anderson stationed there settles himself under the ball and reverse cups it in front of his face. All of a sudden, England are back in the game here.

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Brilliant grab by Joe Root and another Aussie batter has fallen prey to the short ball ploy! Broad comes from 'round the wicket and bangs it into the wicket, directs it at the batter. Travis Head rises and looks to fend it on the leg side. He is in no position to do so and ends up lobbing it towards short leg. Joe Root moves well to his left and takes a one-handed stunner. He is delighted and so are his teammates. Australia have now lost half their side and Stuart Broad has his second wicket of the innings. Also, with that catch, Joe Root becomes the English player with the most number of catches on the field in Test cricket.

Commentary: Drama late on Day 4! Cameron Green comes from 'round the wicket and bangs it in, on off, Ben Duckett backs away to looks to upper cut it fine on the off side. He plays his shot a bit early. The ball comes off the back of the bat and flies down to fine leg who is standing very fine. Mitchell Starc there runs to his left and completes the catch while sliding. He seems confident that he has taken it safely. Ben Duckett starts to trudge off but the umpires ask him to wait as they want to ensure it is a clean take. The replays show that the ball has dragged on the turf while Starc has the ball in his left palm. However, the umpire deems that Starc was not in control of the ball and Ben Duckett survives late in the day.

Commentary: OUT! RUN OUT! Smart work by Alex Carey and Jonny Bairstow looks absolutely stunned! Cameron Green bangs it in yet again, on middle, Jonny Bairstow ducks and starts walking out of the crease thinking that the umpire has called for the over. Alex Carey, behind the stumps, collects the ball and underarms it at the batter's end. He hits the wickets and the Australian players start celebrating. The third umpire is called into action and the side-on replays confirm that Bairstow was way out of his crease when the throw hit. Bairstow is shell-shocked by what has happened but has to make his way back now.  Boos around the ground but Australia have played by the rules here. You cannot venture out of your crease unless the ball is declared dead. In this case, Carey was in the process of throwing the ball at the stumps. The Aussies are on top!
Default_Commentary: 51.6: Cameron Green to Jonny Bairstow, OUT! st Alex Carey b Cameron Green.
